comments: Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) reaches in and initiates contact to Quickley's (TOR) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) briefly grasps Barrett's (TOR) arm and immediately releases prior to attempting to establish a screening position.
Dort (OKC) is in the paint for at or about three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Wiggins (OKC) clamps and holds Poeltl's (TOR) arm, which affects his ability to pursue the rebound.
Wiggins (OKC) slightly extends his arms into Barnes' (TOR) body as he sets the pick, which does not affect Barnes' ability to defend.
Schroder (TOR) briefly places his hand to Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) body during the drive, which he is able to move through.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) brushes Quickley's (TOR) off-arm during the drive as the contact that occurs is marginal.
Wiggins (OKC) deflects the ball during Quickley's (TOR) attempt to pass at the end of the drive.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) releases from Barrett (TOR) during the drive as the contact that occurs does not affect Barrett's ability to defend.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) maintains his pivot foot prior to releasing his pass.
Barnes (TOR) is moving alongside Dort's (OKC) path and the body contact that occurs as they come together during the drive is marginal.
Giddey (OKC) cleanly deflects the ball during Barrett's (TOR) dribble, any additional contact is considered incidental.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Barrett's (TOR) body slides out of bounds while he is still in possession of the ball. Possession is correctly awarded to OKC.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) establishes himself in Quickley's (TOR) path and collapses his arm as he absorbs the incoming contact during the screen.
Quickley (TOR) contests the layup attempt and the body contact that  occurs with Wiggins (OKC) after the release is marginal.
Poeltl (TOR) extends his forearm and dislodges Dort (OKC) from his rebounding position, which affects his ability to pursue the loose ball.
Poeltl (TOR) is retracting when he absorbs the contact from Holmgren (OKC) during the drive as the body contact that occurs is marginal as Holmgren loses his balance.
Dort (OKC) reaches in and briefly places his arm on Quickley's (TOR) body as he attempts to deflect the ball, which Quickley moves through.
Dort (OKC) does not establish a legal guarding position in Barrett's (TOR) path when he absorbs the incoming contact during the drive.
Poeltl (TOR) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Holmgren (OKC) cleanly blocks Quickley's (TOR) jump shot attempt.
Holmgren (OKC) and Barrett (TOR) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
TOR commits a 24 second shot-clock violation.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) cleanly deflects the ball during Quickley's (TOR) attempt to pass at the end of the drive.
Trent Jr. (TOR) slides his arm off Gilgeous-Alexander's (TOR) body as both players attempt to get to the loose ball.
Barrett (TOR) brushes Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) body as he starts his upward shooting motion, which is marginal and is able to avoid further contact during Gilgeous-Alexander's jump shot attempt.
Quickley (TOR) recovers the loose ball before it goes out of bounds.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) cleanly blocks Trent Jr.'s (TOR) jump shot attempt prior to the legal high-five contact that occurs after the release.
Williams (TOR) briefly places his hand on Trent Jr.'s (TOR) shoulder, which he removes as he gets to the loose ball during the rebound.
Barnes (TOR) reaches in and initiates contact to Holmgren's (OKC) after securing the rebound.
Schroder (TOR) is in a legal guarding position when Dort (OKC) dribbles the ball off his foot.
Dort (OKC) cleanly blocks the shot attempt before it touches the backboard.

Replay review of the foul called on Dort (OKC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Dort (OKC) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Schroder's (TOR) body prior to making contact with the ball, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Barnes (TOR) is actively guarding an opponent within three seconds of entering the lane.
Giddey (OKC) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes one step before releasing the pass.
Barnes (TOR) contests Wiggins's (OKC) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Barnes (TOR) swipes down and initiates contact to Giddey's (OKC) off-arm during his driving shot attempt.
Barrett (TOR) briefly places his hand to Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) body at the start of the drive, which he is able to move through.
